1 AN ACT relating to domestic relations.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 508 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) The entering of a judgment of conviction for assault in the first degree or assault
6 in the second degree, or for a felony criminal attempt, conspiracy, facilitation, or
7 solicitation to commit assault in the first degree or assault in the second degree,
8 shall operate as an application for an order of protection issued under KRS
9 Chapter 403 or an interpersonal protective order issued under KRS Chapter 456,
10 as applicable, if the relationship between the defendant and the victim meets the
11 definition of:
12 (a) Family member or member of an unmarried couple as defined in KRS
13 403.720; or
14 (b) Dating relationship as defined in KRS 456.010;
15 unless the victim requests otherwise.
16 (2) Notwithstanding the provisions of KRS Chapter 403 or 456, as applicable:
17 (a) An order of protection or an interpersonal protective order requested under
18 this section may be issued by the court that entered the judgment of
19 conviction;
20 (b) The judgment of conviction shall constitute sufficient cause for entry of the
21 order without the necessity of further proof being taken; and
22 (c) The order may be effective for up to ten (10) years, with further renewals in
23 increments of up to ten (10) years.
24 Section 2. KRS 209A.122 is amended to read as follows:
25 (1) As used in this section:
26 (a) "Center" means the Criminal Justice Statistical Analysis Center created in
27 KRS 15.280;
