UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 611/GA
1 (b) "Corollary victim" means an individual other than the victim who is directly
2 impacted by domestic violence and abuse or dating violence and abuse, either
3 through relationship or proximity;
4 (c) "Domestic violence fatalities" means deaths that occur as a result of domestic
5 violence and abuse or dating violence and abuse, and includes but is not
6 limited to homicides, related suicides, and corollary victims; and
7 (d) "Near fatality" means a crime where serious physical injury as defined in KRS
8 500.080 occurs.
9 (2) The center shall:
10 (a) Collect information on domestic violence fatalities, domestic violence and
11 abuse, and dating violence and abuse within the Commonwealth from
12 subsections (3) to (5) of this section; and
13 (b) Produce an annual report by July 1 of each year and submit the report to[ the]:
14 1. ZeroV[Kentucky Coalition Against Domestic Violence];
15 2. The Governor;
16 3. The cabinet[ for Health and Family Services];
17 4. The Interim Joint Committee on Judiciary;
18 5. The Interim Joint Committee on Families and Children;[ and]
19 6. The Legislative Research Commission;
20 7. The Administrative Office of the Courts; and
21 8. The Office of the Attorney General.
22 ZeroV[The Kentucky Coalition Against Domestic Violence] may provide the
23 agencies listed in subparagraphs 2.[paragraph (b)1.] to 8.[6.] of this
24 paragraph[subsection] with best practices and any other recommendations for
25 public policy by November 15[1] of each year.
26 (3) (a) The Department of Kentucky State Police shall provide the center with:
27 1. The statistical information from all JC-3 forms and all fields on a JC-
