7 Section 3. KRS 15A.190 is amended to read as follows:
8 The [Justice and Public Safety ]cabinet, in consultation with the Cabinet for Health and
9 Family Services, the Kentucky Commission on Women, and any other agency concerned
10 with particular acts of criminal activity, shall:
11 (1) Design[, print,] and make available[distribute] to all law enforcement agencies in
12 the Commonwealth, an electronic [or paper ]uniform reporting form, to be known
13 as the JC-3, which provides statistical information relating to [the ]crimes
14 involving:
15 (a) Domestic violence;
16 (b) Child abuse;
17 (c) Childhood sexual assault or abuse as defined in KRS 413.249;
18 (d) Victimization of the elderly, including but not limited to elder abuse, neglect,
19 and exploitation and other crimes against the elderly; or
20 (e) Any other particular area of criminal activity deemed by the secretary [of
21 justice and public safety ]to require research as to its frequency; and
22 (2) Promulgate administrative regulations[,] in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A[,] to
23 provide that the information required in KRS 209A.122 be provided to the Criminal
24 Justice Statistical Analysis Center.
